caption: Something free to see a replica of the new york statue of liberty. It is also a nice walk my  advice is to look around and you‚Äôll see a nice photo opportunity along the way specially the entry way good view of the Eiffel Tower. The entry is in the middle of a bridge and on top of the bridge they have the metro system that i would recommend taking them to see a different prespective of the Eiffel tower make sure you are going to the right direction.
Nice views of the Eiffel Tower day and night. Access to the Statue of Liberty. Outdoor gym area below the bridge. A+++

Our river cruise started and ended at Pont de Grenelle. It is so convenient to the Eiffel Tower, the Trocadero, Bois de Boulogne and more. Nice walks along the river, with beautiful nights sights of the Eiffel Tower.

Wide bridge..You can see eifal tower and replica of Statue of liberty from this bridge..one of the biggest mall is very near to this bridge.. railway station is very near to this..the view from this bridge is very beautiful..we can see a small island under this bridge and replica of statue of Liberty is placed over there..
It such a beautiful spot to see the Eiffel Tower and Statue of Liberty Replica together

The Pont de Grenelle is one of the bridges that crosses the Seine River and an excellent place to view the Eiffel Tower. This bridge meets the Ile aux Cygnes Island at its tip where a replica of the Statue of Liberty stands. Radio France and the Beaugrenelle shopping centre are also next to the bridge.
What makes it special is the statu of liberty, nice view of the Eiffel tower also.
üíïmust visit spot to enjoy the beauty of paris between sky land and water ‚Ä¶
One of the best day in Paris was the day i walked and enjoy the life at this island. It's amazing and its so romantic. I love it

Paris is such a beautiful and romantic place. So many sites to see and so many places of interest and historical significance. You can tour on busses or on foot or via metro trains, even on a boat via the waterways. Pont De Grenelle is best viewed via a boat. Day and night give different views and perspectives of Pont De Grenelle
Connect√© beau grenelle commercial center to radio France. It is possible to pass through  the ile des cygnes up to Bir-Hakin bridge. Nice walk in the nature inside the city
Great views from the bridge. The small scale replica of the statue of liberty was interesting.
Love this place. It's not like one of those crowded tourists' spots.
If You are looking for ta replica of the Statue of the liberty, this is the right spot in Paris.
Great view of tour Eiffel
Marvellous view on the Eiffel tower in front the Rouelle bridge (RER)
A bridge that you can have a good view of Eiffel Tower at night

This "new bridge" is about 50 years old and replaces an older one!!  The bridge touches down on one of the very few man made islands in the middle of the Seine.  While this is interesting, the "surprise" is seeing a replica of the "Statue of Liberty"-- the original was constructed in France and assembled in New York's Harbour (near Staten Island).  There is also a great Eiffel Tower "photo opp". While somewhat "quirky"-- it makes for an interesting/memorable visit!! I hope that this review has been helpful...

Really beautiful place! I've loved to see the Statue of Liberty and Tour Eiffel all together! hahaha There is also such a little gym here and I think it's a good idea for people who enjoy to workout outside!
Nice old bridge next to the Statue of Liberty.

It was a fun sight from a cruise down the Seine to see Lady Liberty sharing the skyline with the beautiful Eiffel Tower. I was disappointed to see graffiti scrawled on the base, but I feel that's more of reflection of the times we live in, I highly doubt if/when it is cleaned up it will stay cleaned up.
Amazing to see the OG lady liberty. Nice space to take photos, outdoors gym in case you need to exercise. Bit of a walk to get to depending on your stay but worth the nice walk and scenery.

This  was a fun stop. If you want to smell history take the time to explore. The staff are professional, very helpful and genuine . If you have the money shop and experience historical perfume  recipes that can run high in price. But it's  all free to sample and if you read this or are a smart shopper, ask for a free sample, if you can't  afford the perfume  or can't  take the bottle  with you on the flight home. But do stop. It's  part of Paris history.

Can't go to New York to see the Statue of Liberty, never mind, this place gives you the best views of the Statue of Liberty in Paris overlooking the Eiffel Tower. Travel Fact - did you know this statue faces west, towards the NYC Statue of Liberty.
Great place for walk, jogging or exercises. There are some fitness equipment fixed below the flyover. The scaled statue of liberty is anyway the attraction.
Stayed on Botticelli cruise boat moored on the Seine. Only a short walk to the the Eiffel Tower. A good base.

Not really a must visit spot of Paris but if you‚Äôre at the Beaugrenelle shopping center anyways, make sure to enjoy the view on the Seine and Eiffel Tower. Also take a walk on the thin island towards Passy bridge.

I've never been in NEW YORK but always have wanted to see the Statue of Liberty. After watching the movie "National Treasure: Book of Secrets" with Nicolas Cage I found out that the statue is closer than I've expected: In Paris are 4 of them in different sizes. One of those is located (which is appearing in the movie) on the "√éle aux Cygnes" (near of the Eiffel-Tower).  It's a small tip and beyond of all those Tourist locations. It's a short walk from the Eiffel-Tower and you can resting a Little bit on the "√èle" on one of those benches.  The other 2 statues you can find: - Mus√©e des Arts et Metiers - Jardin du Luxembourg. plus one near the Eiffeltower.

I do sports there, mainly calisthenics under the bridge. It's not an amazing place to visit, though the French version of statue of liberty is there. Beaugrenelle mall is also close to there and have many facilities.
Beautiful cruise at the river with 3 language voice guide. The price is normal ;nearly 20euro without lunch or drink.. But be careful for the sun
If you want to take a picture of the small statue of liberty, this is the place, also has some beautiful modern architecture near the bridge.
Nice walk through pathway lined with trees to get to the statue. An outdoor gym is present behind, great for a weekend workout!
There were recomstructions going on so you couldnt make it to the statue. You could look at it only from the distance.
Great view of Eiffel Tower.  Near Isle of Swans where a Statue of Liberty replica is located.
Nice view for the Eiffel Tower from the bridge.
Good spot to workout
If u like walking, stay in grenelle. We loved all the little cafes and authentic welcoming smiles we got
The statue is cool to see, but there was graffiti on the base of it, and a public outdoor gym behind it.
